Observation Details: One goldfinch perched on a tree over the road, giving calls.
Juvenile bird begging for food from an adult male, at a feeder with nyger thistle seed.

Media notes: Contact call of juvenal recently fledged, very short tail, with its head under wing. No obvious adults around.
Observation Details: Jeune ayant récemment quitté le nid. Nous l'avons localisé par ses vocalises régulières et fortes. Il crie, perché sur une branche, caché sous les feuilles, la tête sous l'aile, queue très courte. Aucun adulte à proximité.

Media notes: Female on porch a few feet away; background goldfinch sound is on sunflowers eating of of them
perched 30 ft up on top of a tree; 2 other individuals heard in the background

Background Species: Corvus corax -- Common Raven; Spizella passerina -- Chipping Sparrow

Dryobates pubescens -- Downy Woodpecker; Baeolophus bicolor -- Tufted Titmouse; Melanerpes carolinus -- Red-bellied Woodpecker; Zenaida macroura -- Mourning Dove; Spizella pusilla -- Field Sparrow; Cardinalis cardinalis -- Northern Cardinal; Pipilo erythrophthalmus -- Eastern Towhee
Media notes: Large flock of AMGO visiting Tulip Poplar that has my feeders. I was leaning against the back of the house ca 12 m away from tree but birds did not go to feeder while I was there.  Instead, they remained among the branches of the tree. Number of birds varied as birds came and when but was always about 30-40, minimum. Segments interrupted by approaching car. Final segment interrupted by heat pump switching on.

Locality: Champs et ancien parc à résidus minier
